name: Usain Bolt
details: The Olympic records for the event are 9.63 seconds, set by Usain Bolt in 2012. The world records for the event have been during the Olympics on seven occasions.
title: Men's 100 meters

name: Usain Bolt
details: The Olympic records for the distance are 19.30 seconds for men, set by Usain Bolt in 2008, and 21.34 seconds set by Florence Griffith-Joyner in 1988.
title: Men's 200 meters

name: Wayde Van Niekerk
details: The current men's world record is held by Wayde Van Niekerk of 43.03 seconds. Van Niekerk is also the Olympic record holder.
title: Men's 400 meters

name: Elaine Thompson-Herah
details: The Olympic records for the event are 10.61 seconds, set by Elaine Thompson-Herah in 2021.
title: Women's 100 meters

name: Florence Griffith-Joyner
details: The women's world record holder is Florence Griffith-Joyner of the United States, who ran 21.34 s at the 1988 Summer Olympics.
title: Women's 200 meters

name: Marita Koch
details: The current women's world record is held by Marita Koch, with a time of 47.60 seconds.
title: Women's 400 meters

name: Caeleb Dressel
details: Caeleb Dressel smashed the Olympic record to win 50m freestyle. The American swimmer touched the wall in a time of 21.07.
title: Men's 50 mtr freestyle swimming

name: Cesar Cielo Filho
details: At the 2009 World Championships in Rome, he won the sprint double (50 and 100 metres), crowning his performance with a world record in the 100in a time of 46.91 .
title: Men's 100 mtr freestyle swimming

name: Emma McKeon
details: Australian Emma McKeon stormed to victory in the 50m freestyle event today at Tokyo Aquatics Centre clocking in a blistering time of 23:81 which broke her own Olympic record .
title: Women's 50 mtr freestyle swimming
